As Mental Health Month comes to a close, I wanted to share my personal experience with you all. 💙 It's a story of struggle, but also one of hope and healing. 🌈

💭 For years, I battled with depression, feeling trapped in a dark tunnel with no light in sight. It wasn’t a daily fight but one that set in every couple of weeks and it affected every aspect of my life. But I want you to know that there is light at the end of the tunnel! It took me until my husband asked if I was alright to understand others are seeing how I feel inside. That wake up call was when I got help. 💡

🩺 Seeking help was the turning point. Through therapy and the guidance of my doctor, I found the support I needed to start my journey towards recovery. They helped me understand that depression is not a sign of weakness but rather a medical condition that can be treated. 🙌

💊 Medication was an essential part of my healing process. It's important to note that medication is not a cure-all, but it can significantly alleviate symptoms and provide stability when used in conjunction with therapy for me and my doctor LEXAPRO was the right decision. 🌿

📚 Education and self-awareness are crucial when it comes to mental health. Remember, seeking professional help is not a sign of defeat but an act of strength. I had the hardest time finding a therapist that didn’t have a 6 month waiting list. I found @betterhelp and met a wonderful therapist from Chicago.  Together, we can break the stigma surrounding mental health and support one another on our paths to wellness. 💪

📣 Let's spread awareness, share our stories, and foster a community where no one feels alone in their struggles. 💙 Join me in celebrating the end of Mental Health Month and the beginning of a lifelong journey towards mental well-being. 🌟
